<div id="storytext" class="storytext" style="padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px; padding-top: 10px; text-align: left;"><!-- start story --><p><u><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2-90">Scotty
Doesn’t Know</kw></u></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1-90">Summary:
They didn’t know the other knew</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1-90">Disclaimer:
X-men belongs to Marvel and whoever else, and Scotty Doesn’t Know
belongs to Lustra</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1-90">Warning:
AU, OOC</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1-90">Pairing:
Scogue, some Rogan, Jott, Logan/Jean</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1-90">Set:
Movieverse</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60">A/N:
I know this will probably get me kicked out – or at the very least
chased down by Romy fans, but Scogue is my third favorite Rogue
pairing, and I just </kw><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60">had</kw></i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60"> to write this story! I’m sorry!
</kw><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60">Hides behind table </kw></i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60">Romy still owns my heart if that helps any!
</kw><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60">Dodges various thrown objects </kw></i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-60">Guess not…</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-1-90">A/N2:
Lyrics found at lyricstop</kw></p><p><u><b><kw class="krdwrd-tag-2-90">Scotty
Doesn't Know</kw></b></u></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">The
first time it had been an accident. They were on a routine mission,
searching for a new mutant whose family hadn’t been able to handle
her natural bright pink hair and purple eyes. She had the power to
wake the dead, literally. The professor sent Logan and Jean to get
her, believing they would be best for the job.</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">Scott
and Rogue hadn’t liked it, but they didn’t complain. They trusted
their lovers to be faithful, and the professor knew what he was
doing. But, as these things usually go, Scott and Rogue had been
right not to trust their significant others alone. Logan and Jean had
only been in Michigan for ten minutes before the close proximity in
the X-van was too much. By the time they’d finished, Elly – the
mutant – had been taken by Magneto.</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">Professor
Xavier wasn’t too happy about this, but he was much too worried
about Magneto’s future plans to really lecture them on not paying
close enough attention. Besides, the guilty looks they kept shooting
each other were enough to tell him they understood the repercussions
of their actions. Surely, they would think twice before doing it
again, right?</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">Wrong.</kw></p><p><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-90">Hey!
</kw></i></p><p><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Scotty
doesn't know,</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">That Fionna and me,</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Do it in my van every Sunday.</kw></i></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">The
X-van was much too alluring, and every Sunday they made their way to
the garage while Kurt dragged the other X-men to church. As Jean was
not Catholic, she told Scott she was going to a Methodist church, and
Logan would just grunt that he was going out to drink. Nothing too
unusual there, it was what they always did. But Scott and Rogue had
an idea that something else was up. Jean was the only non-Catholic
that refused to go with them.</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">Still,
they didn’t say anything. To each other or to their lovers, too
afraid were they that their suspicions might be true. But Logan and
Jean would never cheat on them. They loved them! They told them so
every night.</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">But
love didn’t stop Jean from pleasuring Logan with her mouth in ways
that only Rogue had ever done before. And it didn’t stop Logan from
taking Jean in ways that she was sure Scott didn’t even know about.
And the best part of their affair was that Rogue and Scott didn’t
know.</kw></p><p><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">She
tells him she’s in church,</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">But she doesn't go,</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Still she’s
on her knees, and... </kw></i></p><p><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Scotty
doesn’t know, oh.</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Scotty doesn't know-oh.</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">So don't tell
Scotty!</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Scotty doesn't know,</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Scotty doesn't know.</kw><br><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">SO DON'T
TELL SCOTTY!</kw></i></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">It
was official. Scott and Rogue knew it was. They didn’t know that
the other knew, but they knew. And no one else knew that they knew.</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">The
looks Storm and the others would give them were dead giveaways that
they knew about Logan and Jean, but they didn’t want to tell either
of them. They were too afraid of Scott losing his mind, or Rogue
breaking. Rogue was fragile after all, and Jean was all that kept
Scott’s mind together. But that was far from true. They knew, and
they were just fine. Well, except for the heartbreak anyway.</kw></p><p><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">Fionna
