passed by and, still having Logan’s sensitive hearing, had heard
exactly what was going on, perhaps better than Scott who had the
phone to his ear. She shot him a soft, sympathetic smile and left,
while he hurriedly hung up with Jean, hoping that Rogue hadn’t
heard what was going on.</kw></p><p><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-100">He
didn’t think much of the smile she’d shot him; they were becoming
far too common lately. At first he’d thought she knew too, but then
he quickly erased that idea. She’d been looking at him differently
lately, ever since Jean and Logan found pleasure in each other. He
knew it was because Logan wasn’t as into it as he used to be, he
didn’t care as much for Rogue's pleasure as he did his own anymore
. It was because of Jean. He tasted the redhead and became addicted.
It was much the same for Scott, so he could respect her attention
wandering from the hairy jerk to him.</kw></p><p><i><kw class="krdwrd-tag-3-70">We'll
